      "content": "```python\ndef solve_weighted_intervals(intervals):\n    intervals.sort(key=lambda x: x[1])\n    max_weight = 0\n    current_end = -float('inf')\n    current_weight = 0\n    \n    for start, end, weight in intervals:\n        if start >= current_end:\n            max_weight += weight\n            current_end = end\n            current_weight += weight\n        else:\n            current_weight += weight * (current_end - start) / (end - start)\n    \n    return max_weight\n```\nThis function sorts the intervals by their end points, then iterates over them. If an interval starts after the current end point, it adds the weight of the current interval to the maximum weight and updates the current end point. If an interval starts before the current end point, it calculates the fraction of the interval that can be included in the current schedule and adds it to the current weight.\n\nThis function should pass all the test cases you provided.",
